## Overview
This project simulates a realâ€‘world credit decision engine. It combines **financial domain knowledge** (debtâ€‘toâ€‘income ratios, household composition) with **supervised machine learning** to predict loan default risk. The system integrates:

- Data preprocessing & feature engineering  
- Exploratory data analysis with visualisations  
- Multiple ML models (Logistic Regression, Random Forest, XGBoost, AdaBoost, etc.)  
- A **business rule engine** for hard reject/approve decisions  
- A **risk scoring module** that outputs a 0â€“100 risk score  
- An **interactive widget** to test custom loan applications  

---

## Features
- **Automated data cleaning** â€“ handles missing values, standardises formats.  
- **Financial ratio calculations** â€“ DTI, PTI, income per person, loanâ€‘toâ€‘income, etc.  
- **Householdâ€‘level analysis** â€“ number of earners, dependents, coâ€‘applicant impact.  
- **Machine learning pipeline** â€“ preprocesses categorical/numerical features, trains and evaluates 6 classifiers.  
- **Model persistence** â€“ saves the best model and metadata with `joblib`.  
- **Ruleâ€‘based preâ€‘screening** â€“ fastâ€‘track, automatic rejection for clear violations.  
- **Risk scoring** â€“ composite score based on credit history, DTI, PTI, income, and ML confidence.  
- **Interactive Jupyter widgets** â€“ test your own loan application instantly.  
- **Performance dashboard** â€“ ROC curve, confusion matrix, feature importance, business impact analysis.

